div.p:
"I live to learn their story, who suffered for my sake;
To emulate their glory, and follow in their wake;
Bards, patriots, martyrs, sages, and noble of all ages,
Whose deeds crown History's pages, and Time's great volume make.

formula.p:
Heigh! I guess he wasn't very sick;
For see! he's round in "double quick";
But alopath holds'em for weeks, six or seven,
When bleeding, calomel, and antimony are given.

section.p:
"Live for something;" slothful be no longer, look around for some employ;
Labor always makes you stronger, and also gives you sweetest joy.
Idle hands are always weary; faithful hearts are always gay;
Life for us, should not be dreary; not can it, to the active, every day.
